LEGAL_PUBLIC.TERMS_S8_BODY:
You agree not to:
• Harass, threaten, abuse, or harm any other user;
• Post or share offensive, defamatory, misleading, or illegal content;
• Attempt to arrange payments with Tutors outside the Platform in order to circumvent Barnabi's fees;
• Use automated tools to scrape, crawl, or manipulate the Platform;
• Impersonate any person or misrepresent your qualifications;
• Violate any applicable law or regulation.

Violation of these rules may result in immediate account suspension or termination.

LEGAL_PUBLIC.PRIVACY_S3_BODY:
We use your information to:

• Create and manage your account and deliver the services you request;
• Process bookings and payments and issue refunds or credits;
• Match Students with suitable Tutors based on language, level, and availability;
• Personalise your experience, including lesson recommendations and learning-plan suggestions;
• Send service-related notifications such as booking confirmations, reminders, and account alerts;
• Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and safety incidents;
• Comply with legal obligations, enforce our Terms, and respond to lawful requests from authorities;
• Improve the Platform through analytics and user research.

LEGAL_PUBLIC.PRIVACY_S7_BODY:
Barnabi uses cookies and similar technologies for:

• Authentication — keeping you logged in across sessions;
• Session management — maintaining your preferences and state;
• Analytics — understanding aggregate usage patterns to improve the Platform.

You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may limit certain features such as staying logged in. We do not serve behavioural advertising cookies.

LEGAL_PUBLIC.PRIVACY_S9_BODY:
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

• Access — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you;
• Correction — ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data;
• Deletion — request that we delete your personal data, subject to legal retention requirements;
• Portability — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format;
• Objection or restriction — object to or ask us to restrict certain types of processing;
• Withdraw consent — where processing is based on consent, withdraw it at any time without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing.

To exercise these rights, use in-app support or the settings in your account.
